Doesn't just work for
him, it works for you.

33:28.020 --> 33:30.190
Okay, I don't understand
a word you're saying.

33:30.190 --> 33:32.020
They're gonna run
Colin for senator.

33:32.020 --> 33:34.400
That's why he's
working as an AUSA.

33:34.400 --> 33:36.060
It's a stepping stone to office.

33:36.060 --> 33:38.190
So are you.

33:38.190 --> 33:42.190
The hot black girlfriend?
It's a demographic dream.

33:42.190 --> 33:44.850
Ask de Blasio.

33:52.440 --> 33:55.020
Thanks.

33:55.020 --> 33:57.190
Lucca, what's going on?
Where you going?

33:57.190 --> 33:58.770
Uh work. I got to go.

33:58.770 --> 34:00.060
An emergency.

34:00.060 --> 34:01.560
All right, well, I'll take you.

34:01.560 --> 34:04.020
No, it's fine.
I called for a Lyft.

34:04.020 --> 34:05.270
Apologize to
your parents for me.

34:05.270 --> 34:07.020
Work of a lawyer, right?

34:09.560 --> 34:11.230
Colin, come in here!

34:20.020 --> 34:23.139
I-I was thinking...
Triage nurse to E.R.

34:23.139 --> 34:23.889
Oh, my God, Henry.

34:23.891 --> 34:24.639
Oh, my gosh.

34:24.639 --> 34:26.190
What were you doing?

34:26.190 --> 34:27.560
We have people
to check the roof.

34:27.560 --> 34:29.350
Look... Oh, God.
Look at you.

34:29.350 --> 34:31.020
I'm fine. It's nothing, really.
It's-it's...

34:31.020 --> 34:31.710
It's nothing.

34:31.710 --> 34:32.400
It's your leg.

34:32.400 --> 34:34.350
And your back.
I-It's everything.

34:34.350 --> 34:36.600
Oh, my God, if I lost you,

34:36.600 --> 34:38.100
I don't know what I'd do.

34:38.100 --> 34:39.900
Aw.

34:39.900 --> 34:41.270
And what were you doing there?

34:42.900 --> 34:45.100
I wanted... I wanted to see Dad.

34:45.100 --> 34:46.690
Oh, thank God.

34:46.690 --> 34:48.730
If he, if he had
been lying there

34:48.730 --> 34:51.190
all night...

34:59.270 --> 35:02.520
You had Jax bring you here?

35:02.520 --> 35:05.440
I d... I didn't, I didn't
want to wait for a cab.

35:05.440 --> 35:08.520
I was too upset to drive myself.

35:08.520 --> 35:10.980
You have to end it, Mom.

35:10.980 --> 35:13.520
What difference does it make
if Jax drove me here?

35:13.520 --> 35:15.520
Did you hear what I just said?

35:15.520 --> 35:17.350
You have to end it.

35:17.350 --> 35:18.730
End what?

35:18.730 --> 35:20.310
Stop that.

35:20.310 --> 35:22.690
You know what I mean.

35:25.020 --> 35:27.230
Whatever you think you know
about your uncle and I...

35:27.230 --> 35:29.400
It doesn't matter what I think.

35:29.400 --> 35:31.310
It's what my father thinks.

35:31.310 --> 35:34.190
How do you know what he thinks?

35:41.020 --> 35:43.850
What...

35:43.850 --> 35:47.310
"I don't write this
out of feeling wronged,

35:47.310 --> 35:50.690
"that because my wife
slept with my brother,

35:50.690 --> 35:52.520
"I'm owed something.

35:52.520 --> 35:56.520
"It's I who's cheated my wife...

35:56.520 --> 35:58.980
"out of what it feels like

35:58.980 --> 36:02.350
to be loved by someone
you love in return."

36:04.350 --> 36:06.640
What is that?

36:06.640 --> 36:10.770
"Just like I've cheated
my daughter of being able

36:10.770 --> 36:12.850
"to hold her head up

36:12.850 --> 36:16.520
"and not be held accountable
for the mistakes...

36:16.520 --> 36:18.640
"the crimes... of her father.

36:18.640 --> 36:24.100
"I love these two people
more than anyone in the world.

36:24.100 --> 36:26.270
"I just want them to be happy,

36:26.270 --> 36:30.350
"and the best chance
of that happening is for me

36:30.350 --> 36:32.940
to clear out
and let them."

36:35.640 --> 36:39.770
He made me swear I wouldn't
tell you he tried to do it.

36:39.770 --> 36:41.770
You can't say anything.

36:57.810 --> 37:00.230
How's Henry?

37:00.230 --> 37:01.730
Go away.

37:01.730 --> 37:05.560
I just want to check... Go away.

37:07.480 --> 37:09.400
Look, with the
vote six hours away,

37:09.400 --> 37:10.940
here's where we stand.

37:10.940 --> 37:15.190
Evelyn says her expense
allowance is "stingy."

37:15.190 --> 37:16.500
Stingy.

37:16.501 --> 37:17.810
She'd like an increase.

37:17.810 --> 37:19.270
And Mark feels
the firm has lost track

37:19.270 --> 37:20.600
of its civil rights roots.

37:20.600 --> 37:22.310
I love how
Mr. Reddick talks.

37:22.310 --> 37:23.640
Truly.

37:23.640 --> 37:25.480
But we do
more good in the world,

37:25.480 --> 37:27.270
we have the capital to do good.

37:27.270 --> 37:29.520
Trump's America sure ain't
my America. Is it yours?

37:29.520 --> 37:31.480
No, we got to keep on fighting.

37:31.480 --> 37:34.020
So now that we're making more
money, we don't have to be

37:34.020 --> 37:35.850
so stingy
on the expense accounts.

37:35.850 --> 37:38.690
That's the way we felt like
in, uh, Selma, you know?

37:38.690 --> 37:42.350
There's an easier way to live.

37:42.350 --> 37:44.440
Each one of us

37:44.440 --> 37:47.310
is not as strong
as we are collectively.

37:47.310 --> 37:48.980
Right?

37:48.980 --> 37:51.190
Is that fair enough?
That's not rocket science.

37:51.190 --> 37:53.020
Hi.

37:53.020 --> 37:55.020
Yeah, the gentleman behind me...

38:25.440 --> 38:26.850
Sorry.

38:37.940 --> 38:40.270
As you can see, Mr. Kovac,

38:40.270 --> 38:43.100
these are the readouts
from the two fitness trackers...

38:43.100 --> 38:44.520
I hate this thing.

38:44.520 --> 38:46.400
...and the breathing
doesn't match.

38:46.400 --> 38:47.850
Your client's heart rate
is increasing,

38:47.850 --> 38:51.230
and Pastor Jeremiah's
is decreasing.

38:51.230 --> 38:54.020
That is not indicative
of sexual relations.

38:54.020 --> 38:56.520
Oh, my God, you got me.

38:56.520 --> 38:58.770
If I were you,
I would drop this suit, sir,

38:58.770 --> 39:01.350
or you'll be facing
a devastating countersuit.

39:03.350 --> 39:06.230
You know the only problem
you have, Diane?

39:06.230 --> 39:08.690
I can't wait.

39:08.690 --> 39:11.730
Paul can identify
a distinguishing mark

39:11.730 --> 39:13.900
on the good pastor's dick.

39:13.900 --> 39:15.560
Now <i>that</i>

39:15.560 --> 39:18.640
is indicative
of sexual relations.

39:18.640 --> 39:21.600
You still want to countersue
and take this to open court?

39:21.600 --> 39:22.940
Hmm?

39:22.940 --> 39:23.940
You just let me know.

39:30.190 --> 39:32.940
I will not disrobe.

39:32.940 --> 39:36.060
It's the easiest way
to prove him wrong, Rev.

39:36.060 --> 39:38.770
Now you don't have
a birthmark on your penis?

39:38.770 --> 39:40.690
No, I don't.

39:40.690 --> 39:41.565
So he's lying?

39:41.566 --> 39:42.440
Yes.

39:42.440 --> 39:45.190
The difficulty is,
Pastor, if you don't

39:45.190 --> 39:48.100
disrobe, this will
make you look guilty.

39:48.100 --> 39:49.520
I understand that.

39:49.520 --> 39:50.940
I am not disrobing.

39:50.940 --> 39:53.850
You can take the camera

39:53.850 --> 39:56.480
and take a photo of yourself.

39:58.520 --> 40:01.980
I spent my whole life fighting,

40:01.980 --> 40:06.980
fighting for the dignity
that was denied our forebears.

40:06.980 --> 40:08.600
They were treated like this.

40:08.600 --> 40:10.230
I will not be.

40:10.230 --> 40:11.770
That's what he's counting on,

40:11.770 --> 40:14.100
this little, uh... pissant.

40:14.100 --> 40:17.230
He is blackmailing you,
and he's counting on the fact

40:17.230 --> 40:21.020
that you have too much pride
to prove that he's a liar.

40:21.020 --> 40:24.310
Then he's smart, and accurate,

40:24.310 --> 40:25.980
because I won't.

40:25.980 --> 40:28.270
Then I think you should pay him.

40:28.270 --> 40:30.980
He's gonna ruin
your reputation, Reverend.

40:30.980 --> 40:33.350
All that dignity
that you fought for,

40:33.350 --> 40:35.140
it will disappear
just like that.

40:35.140 --> 40:36.310
Do you believe him?

40:36.310 --> 40:37.600
It's not about what I believe,

40:37.600 --> 40:38.900
it's about what we can prove.

40:38.900 --> 40:41.480
That's not what I asked.

40:41.480 --> 40:44.270
Reverend...

40:44.270 --> 40:46.770
I have been around
too long to know better than

40:46.770 --> 40:50.230
to expect anything from my
heroes other than feet of clay.

40:52.810 --> 40:54.940
I don't care
one way or the other.

40:54.940 --> 40:57.730
I just want to beat
this son of a bitch.

40:57.730 --> 41:00.520
The fitness tracker
links to an app

41:00.520 --> 41:01.850
which tracks your routes,
like this.

41:01.850 --> 41:04.520
That's me, running
around the office,

41:04.520 --> 41:06.440
talking to all of the assistants
about who their bosses

41:06.440 --> 41:07.170
are voting for.

41:07.171 --> 41:07.900
And?

41:07.900 --> 41:09.770
I was able to pull up
Paul Johnson's tracking data

41:09.770 --> 41:10.770
for the past two months.

41:14.400 --> 41:17.400
When Paul goes jogging,
it's fairly random.

41:17.400 --> 41:19.400
No two routes
appear to be the same.

41:19.400 --> 41:22.060
But about two weeks ago,
a pattern started to emerge.

41:22.060 --> 41:24.100
Two or three times a week,
Paul's routes included

41:24.100 --> 41:25.560
a pit stop at Kovac's office.

41:25.560 --> 41:27.400
Well, that makes sense;
he's his lawyer.

41:27.400 --> 41:29.400
No. Paul didn't
claim to have a lawyer

41:29.400 --> 41:31.850
until we served him
the eviction notice.

41:31.850 --> 41:33.730
Good.

41:33.730 --> 41:35.770
We need to look
deeper into Kovac.

41:35.770 --> 41:38.060
Any lawsuits, past crimes.

41:38.060 --> 41:40.060
See what you can find.

41:40.060 --> 41:41.310
Perfect timing.

41:41.311 --> 41:42.560
Yeah.

41:42.560 --> 41:43.560
Uh, Ms. Stanway?

41:43.560 --> 41:44.900
Yes?

41:44.900 --> 41:46.400
Hi. We're from the law firm
Reddick/Boseman.

41:46.400 --> 41:47.770
We were wondering
if we can ask you

41:47.770 --> 41:49.770
a few questions
about Gabe Kovac.

41:49.770 --> 41:51.400
Records show you sued him for
an assault a few years back.

41:51.400 --> 41:52.850
Yeah, we settled and I
dropped the charges.

41:52.850 --> 41:54.400
Can you tell us what happened?

41:54.400 --> 41:56.190
I'm sorry. I signed a
nondisclosure agreement.

41:56.190 --> 41:57.850
What if we promise not to tell?

41:57.850 --> 41:59.520
Hey, you never know.

41:59.520 --> 42:01.400
- Sorry. If you'll excuse me.
- Uh, Why would Kovac

42:01.400 --> 42:03.350
- Have you sign an NDA?
- He didn't. His lawyer did.

42:03.350 --> 42:04.900
And it wasn't with him.

42:04.900 --> 42:07.730
It was with his employer,
First Charter Choice.

42:07.730 --> 42:09.400
- First Charter Choice.
- What's that?

42:09.400 --> 42:11.190
It's an alt-right cause.

42:11.190 --> 42:13.100
Okay, am I missing something?

42:13.100 --> 42:15.020
No, but I was.

42:15.020 --> 42:15.730
Who you calling?

42:15.731 --> 42:16.440
Adrian.

42:16.440 --> 42:18.440
They're going
into negotiations. Come on.

42:19.900 --> 42:21.690
Got it, Jay.

42:21.690 --> 42:22.560
Thanks.

42:22.560 --> 42:23.560
Good work.

42:23.560 --> 42:24.640
Anytime.

42:25.850 --> 42:27.480
Oh. Uh, come on in, gentlemen.

42:29.770 --> 42:33.600
So, I guess you
finally came to your senses,

42:33.600 --> 42:34.900
and are ready to settle.

42:34.900 --> 42:36.190
Are you at all familiar

42:36.190 --> 42:37.980
with Rule 1.7 of the ARDC

42:37.980 --> 42:39.770
Code of Ethics,
Mr. Kovac?

42:39.770 --> 42:42.600
It's been a while since
I studied for the bar.

42:42.600 --> 42:45.560
Why don't, uh... why don't
you sum it up for me.

42:45.560 --> 42:48.810
Conflicts of interest between
attorneys and their clients

42:48.810 --> 42:50.690
may result in disbarment.

42:50.690 --> 42:54.730
Do I have a kind of conflict
of interest with Paul?

42:54.730 --> 42:56.900
We're aware that you have
done business with, uh,

42:56.900 --> 42:58.850
Mr. Selkirk's
right-wing legal foundation,

42:58.850 --> 43:00.230
First Charter Choice.

43:00.230 --> 43:01.520
And we're also aware

43:01.520 --> 43:03.940
that Selkirk subsidized
this "lawsuit,"

43:03.940 --> 43:05.480
to embarrass the good reverend.

43:05.480 --> 43:07.350
You're taking money
from the alt-right, Mr. Kovac,

43:07.350 --> 43:09.350
and you edited
the drug dealer from that video.

43:09.350 --> 43:10.640
You know what?

43:10.640 --> 43:14.900
I think we're, uh...
we're about done here.

43:14.900 --> 43:18.350
And we are prepared to file
a civil suit against you

43:18.350 --> 43:21.140
and your client...
for extortion!

43:21.140 --> 43:22.640
Have a good day, now!

43:37.020 --> 43:39.020
Why aren't you
answering my calls?

43:39.020 --> 43:40.230
I've been busy.

43:40.230 --> 43:42.060
My family is insane.

43:42.060 --> 43:44.520
Why do you think I didn't
introduce you to them earlier?

43:44.520 --> 43:46.560
This isn't about your family.

43:46.560 --> 43:49.020
It's about this relationship.
It's run its course.

43:49.020 --> 43:50.640
I disagree.

43:50.640 --> 43:52.560
That's your right.

43:52.560 --> 43:55.900
I'm not sure what you're
looking for, but I'm not her.

43:55.900 --> 43:58.810
I'm not an accessory,
I'm not a... trophy.

43:58.810 --> 44:00.900
I'm sure as hell not a wife.

44:00.900 --> 44:03.190
And I never treated
you that way.

44:03.190 --> 44:05.810
And if anyone ever does,
they have no place in my life.

44:05.810 --> 44:08.850
You're making this a bigger deal
than it needs to be.

44:10.730 --> 44:12.060
I don't like your tone.

44:12.060 --> 44:13.480
There is no tone.

44:13.480 --> 44:15.730
We had fun.

44:15.730 --> 44:18.230
Both knew it wasn't for life.

44:18.230 --> 44:20.140
We don't do "for life."

44:22.100 --> 44:23.560
I have to go.

44:52.730 --> 44:54.900
Imani's voting for Reddick,
but you have

44:54.900 --> 44:57.140
Calvin Story,
Eunice and Tommy Neville.

44:57.140 --> 44:59.770
By my count, you're up one.

44:59.770 --> 45:00.770
Good. Thank you.

45:00.770 --> 45:01.770
Julius.

45:01.770 --> 45:03.230
Saved you a seat.

45:03.230 --> 45:03.835
Fucking Julius?

45:03.836 --> 45:04.440
Thanks, Carl.

45:04.440 --> 45:06.230
Yeah.

45:06.230 --> 45:08.440
Carl.

45:08.440 --> 45:12.060
Julius Cain is leaving the firm.
He is ineligible to vote.

45:12.060 --> 45:14.270
Article 12,
Subsection D puts forth

45:14.270 --> 45:16.020
that full voting rights
will remain in force

45:16.020 --> 45:18.980
through the last day
of the partner's pay period,

45:18.980 --> 45:21.230
which I believe is Thursday.

45:21.230 --> 45:22.640
Well, then
shall we commence, uh,

45:22.640 --> 45:24.100
casting the ballots?

45:33.560 --> 45:37.480
11 for Adrian and 12 for Carl.

45:37.480 --> 45:39.980
I want the room polled.

45:39.980 --> 45:42.690
For what reason? You lost.

45:42.690 --> 45:45.560
I want to vote for the removal
of Adrian Boseman.

45:45.560 --> 45:46.940
Wait.

45:46.940 --> 45:49.060
I didn't vote.

45:49.060 --> 45:50.480
But I want to now.

45:50.480 --> 45:51.520
Eh, it's too late.

45:51.520 --> 45:53.190
No, it's not.

45:53.190 --> 45:57.060
Carl, you said this was a battle

45:57.060 --> 45:59.600
between the firm's heart
and its head.

45:59.600 --> 46:01.400
But it's not.

46:01.400 --> 46:03.940
It's about the past
or the future.

46:06.400 --> 46:09.100
Your past glories
have a lot to teach us,

46:09.100 --> 46:13.060
but this... this is now.

46:13.060 --> 46:16.440
The fights are now, and Adrian
knows how to fight them.

46:19.270 --> 46:21.770
I vote for Adrian.

46:25.560 --> 46:27.730
So here we are.

46:27.730 --> 46:29.350
We're split.

46:29.350 --> 46:30.560
Yep.

46:30.560 --> 46:32.520
50/50.

46:32.520 --> 46:34.900
This should be fun.

46:34.900 --> 46:37.690
Hmm. That's the problem
with the world today, huh?

46:37.690 --> 46:39.270
You think the fights
are different now.

46:39.270 --> 46:42.190
But you're wrong.

46:42.190 --> 46:44.560
They're exactly the same.

47:04.400 --> 47:05.600
May I?

47:23.850 --> 47:25.560
To idealism.

47:25.560 --> 47:27.190
Hmm.

47:27.190 --> 47:29.980
And pragmatism.

